    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Dynamic Programming</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: monospace;\n            background-color: white;\n        }\n        input, button {\n            width: 20%;\n            height: 20%;\n            padding: 5px;\n            margin: 5px;\n            border: 1px solid black;\n        }\n        button {\n            background-color: #4CAF50;\n            color: white;\n            padding: 5px 10px;\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n        }\n        button:hover {\n            background-color: #3e8e41;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Dynamic Programming</h1>\n    <p>This is a simple example of dynamic programming.</p>\n    <h2>Problem:</h2>\n    <p>Find the maximum sum of a subarray of size k.</p>\n    <input id=\"k\" type=\"number\" value=\"3\" min=\"1\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\">\n    <button id=\"solve\">Solve</button>\n    <p id=\"result\"></p>\n\n    <script>\n        let k = parseInt(document.getElementById('k').value);\n        let dp = new Array(11).fill(0).map(() => new Array(11).fill(-Infinity));\n        function solve() {\n            let result = '';\n            for (let i = 0; i <= 10; i++) {\n                for (let j = 0; j <= 10; j++) {\n                    if (i + j >= k) {\n                        dp[i][j] = Math.max(dp[i][j], dp[i][j - 1] + i === 0 ? 0 : dp[i - 1][j]);\n                    }\n                    result += (i === 0 ? '' : ', ') + dp[i][j] + ' ';\n                }\n            }\n            document.getElementById('result').innerHTML = result.trim();\n        }\n        solve();\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
